---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import HelpCard from '../components/HelpCard.astro';
import EmailBlock from '../components/EmailBlock.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="331 Maple St — Prospect Lefferts Gardens">

<!-- ─── HERO ─── -->
<section class="hero">
  <Nav activePage="home" />

  <div class="hero-body">
    <p class="eyebrow"><span>⚠ Demolition Imminent — Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn</span></p>
    <h1 class="hero-headline">
      Stop the<br /><em>Tower.</em>
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      A private equity developer is planning to demolish the parish school at 335 Maple St and replace it with a <strong>12-story, 99-unit luxury tower — with zero affordable units.</strong> A personalized email to the church or your elected officials carries more weight than anything else you can do right now.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="#emails" class="btn-primary">Send an Email</a>
      <a href="#petition" class="btn-outline">Sign the Petition</a>
      <button class="btn-share" id="hero-share">↗ Share This Page</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── ABOUT ─── -->
<section class="about" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="before-after reveal">
      <div class="ba-card">
        <div class="ba-label ba-label-before">What Will Be Lost</div>
        <img src="/331mapleparish.png" alt="335 Maple St Parish School, built 1909" />
        <p class="ba-caption">335 Maple St Parish School, built 1909. Currently slated for demolition.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="ba-card">
        <div class="ba-label ba-label-after">What Would Replace It</div>
        <img src="/331maplemockup.png" alt="Developer rendering of proposed 12-story tower" />
        <p class="ba-caption">Developer rendering of the proposed 12-story, 99-unit building. No affordable units.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-grid reveal" style="margin-top:4rem;">
      <div class="about-body reveal">
        <p class="section-label">The Issue</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">What is happening <em>on Maple Street?</em></h2>
        <p>St. Francis of Assisi Church on Nostrand Ave has signed a <strong>99-year lease</strong> with private equity-backed developer <strong>Candor Capital</strong> to demolish the 335 Maple St. Parish School — built in 1909 — and replace it with a 12-story, 118-foot, 99-unit market-rate complex with <strong>zero affordable units.</strong></p>
        <p>What makes it worse: <strong>Candor Capital showed the Church a 6-story mock-up before signing the lease, then secretly filed for a 12-story building with the DOB.</strong> Father Tom tried to appeal for a shorter building, but his hands were tied.</p>
        <p>The developer has already broken the law — demolition began in January without permits, a <strong>Stop Work Order was issued</strong>, and they've violated it repeatedly, racking up $30,000 in fines.</p>
        <p>Prospect Lefferts Gardens has never received the contextual zoning protections that <strong>Park Slope, Windsor Terrace, and Kensington</strong> have had for years. This building would be flatly illegal one neighborhood over. PLG has been asking for the same protections since 2008.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <ul class="facts-list">
          <li><span class="fact-icon">⬤</span><div><span class="fact-strong">Developer showed Church a 6-story mock-up</span>, then secretly filed for 12 stories without the Church's knowledge</div></li>
          <li><span class="fact-icon">⬤</span><div><span class="fact-strong">12-story, 118-foot luxury tower</span> — dwarfing a neighborhood of 4–5 story buildings</div></li>
          <li><span class="fact-icon">⬤</span><div><span class="fact-strong">99 units, zero affordable housing</span> — no community benefit whatsoever</div></li>
          <li><span class="fact-icon">⬤</span><div><span class="fact-strong">Illegal demolition already attempted</span> — Stop Work Order issued; $30K fine; violations ongoing</div></li>
          <li><span class="fact-icon">⬤</span><div><span class="fact-strong">Diocese stonewalling elected officials</span> — no response to meeting requests for 30+ days</div></li>
          <li><span class="fact-icon">⬤</span><div><span class="fact-strong">PLG has no contextual zoning</span> — unlike Park Slope, Windsor Terrace, and Kensington next door</div></li>
          <li><span class="fact-icon">⬤</span><div><span class="fact-strong">335 Maple St. Parish School built 1909</span> — on the National Register of Historic Places</div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── URGENCY ─── -->
<section class="urgency-section" id="urgency">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal" style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <p class="section-label">How We Got Here</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">The clock is <em>running out.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="urgency-grid urgency-grid--timeline-only">
      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="tl-dot">✓</div>
          <div class="tl-text"><strong>Sep 2025 — 99-Year Lease Signed</strong><span>Candor Capital showed Church a 6-story mock-up, then secretly filed for 12 stories with DOB</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="tl-dot">✓</div>
          <div class="tl-text"><strong>Oct–Nov 2025 — Community Mobilizes</strong><span>Canvassing from Sterling to Clarkson Ave; hundreds of petition signatures collected; reps engaged</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="tl-dot">✓</div>
          <div class="tl-text"><strong>Dec 2025 — Meeting with Representatives</strong><span>Council Member Joseph and Assemblymember Cunningham agree to investigate legality; Church refuses to attend</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="tl-dot">✓</div>
          <div class="tl-text"><strong>Jan 2026 — Illegal Demolition Attempted</strong><span>Workers with sledgehammers begin tearing down school without permits. DOB issues Stop Work Order. $30K fine levied.</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="tl-dot">✓</div>
          <div class="tl-text"><strong>Feb 2026 — Diocese Sends Uninformed Liaison</strong><span>Church finally agrees to a meeting but sends a political liaison with no knowledge of the development</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="tl-dot" style="background:var(--accent); color:#000;">!</div>
          <div class="tl-text"><strong>Mar 2026 — Developer Clearing Violations NOW</strong><span>Stop Work Order violations being cleared. Church still not responding to reps. 600+ signatures and counting.</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="tl-dot dim">?</div>
          <div class="tl-text"><strong>Demolition — Imminent</strong><span>Once the Maple Street Parish School comes down, the developer has everything they need to build</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── NEIGHBOR QUOTES ─── -->

<section class="quotes-strip">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="quotes-header reveal">
      <p class="section-label" style="color:rgba(245,239,224,0.4);">In Their Own Words</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Real neighbors. <em>Real stakes.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="quotes-grid">
      <blockquote class="pull-quote reveal">
        <p>"This building of this height would block the natural sunlight my family has had in this house for the last 50+ years. Build with respect to the communities you come into."</p>
        <footer><strong>Calleen</strong><span>Lincoln Road</span></footer>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote class="pull-quote reveal">
        <p>"We need all new housing built with contextual height restrictions to respect and preserve the existing neighborhoods. This proposed building violates the neighborhood context and would significantly change the nature of this neighborhood detrimentally."</p>
        <footer><strong>Margaret</strong><span>Midwood Street</span></footer>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote class="pull-quote reveal">
        <p>"The amount of development I've seen without consulting the local community has only resulted in 'affordable' apartments that locals can't afford — a money grab by developers while destroying the local neighborhood."</p>
        <footer><strong>Diana</strong><span>Midwood Street</span></footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
    <div class="quotes-cta reveal">
      <a href="/voices" class="btn-outline">Read All 17 Neighbor Voices →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── PETITION ─── -->
<section class="petition-section" id="petition">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="petition-grid">
      <div class="petition-intro reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Take Action</p>
        <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--black);">Sign the <em style="color:rgba(0,0,0,0.4);">petition.</em></h2>
        <p>Over 600 of your neighbors have already signed. <strong>Your address matters</strong> — it shows the community impact is real and local.</p>
        <p>The petition asks our local representatives to have the neighborhood rezoned to mandate contextual height restrictions on new developments, bringing harmony to the historic street scale of Prospect Lefferts Gardens.</p>
        <p>Maple Street is listed on the <strong>National Register of Historic Places</strong> and is made up of single-family homes and prewar buildings no more than 4–5 stories tall. This tower would destroy that forever.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:1.5rem; font-size:0.85rem; color:#6B5E52;">Questions? <a href="#" class="protected-email" style="color:var(--dark-red);">Contact Amy Lin</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="petition-embed-box">
          <iframe
            src="https://form.jotform.com/amyqinglin/331maple"
            title="Sign the Petition"
            height="700"
            allowtransparency="true"
            allow="geolocation; microphone; camera"
            frameborder="0"
            scrolling="yes">
          </iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── EMAIL TEMPLATES ─── -->
<section class="emails-section" id="emails">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="section-label">Email Templates</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Send a message. <em>Make it count.</em></h2>
      <p class="emails-intro">Personalized emails from residents carry real weight. Use these templates as a starting point — customize with your own name and personal connection to the neighborhood for maximum impact.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion reveal">

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-trigger">
          <span class="acc-label"><span class="acc-tag">Church</span> Diocese of Brooklyn &amp; Church Leadership</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <EmailBlock id="email-diocese-1" to="Bishop Robert Brennan" toEmail="bishopofbrooklyn@diobrook.org" subject="Urgent: 331 Maple St Development — Request for Community Meeting" body={`Dear Bishop Brennan,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a resident of Prospect Lefferts Gardens writing to ask you directly to meet with our community about the proposed 12-story development at 331 Maple St.

I love this neighborhood. The scale, history, and character of Prospect Lefferts Gardens are part of what makes it one of Brooklyn's most special communities, and a 12-story market-rate tower with zero affordable units would fundamentally alter that character in a way that cannot be undone.

I am also troubled by serious unresolved questions around the legality of this development — particularly regarding air rights — that deserve transparent, public answers before any demolition proceeds.

Over 600 residents have signed a petition asking the Diocese to come to the table. Council Member Rita Joseph and Assemblymember Brian Cunningham have been requesting a high-level meeting with Church leadership for over a month with no response. With demolition of the 335 Maple St. Parish School imminent, we are running out of time.

A compromise — a shorter building that respects the neighborhood — is still possible, but only if the Church is willing to engage. I respectfully urge you to respond to our representatives' meeting requests and participate in that conversation.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
          <EmailBlock id="email-diocese-2" to="Father Thomas Vassalotti, St. Francis of Assisi" toEmail="fathertomv@gmail.com" subject="331 Maple St — Asking for Your Help" body={`Dear Father Tom,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a resident of Prospect Lefferts Gardens. I am writing because I understand you have tried to advocate for a shorter building at 331 Maple St — and I want to thank you for that.

The community knows your hands have been tied by the Diocese. We are not writing to blame you — we are writing because we need your help. Over 600 neighbors have signed a petition, and our elected officials have been trying to get a meeting with Diocese leadership for over a month with no response. Demolition of the 335 Maple St. Parish School is approaching.

You know this neighborhood. You know what this block means to the people who live here. A 12-story, 99-unit market-rate tower with zero affordable units is not what St. Francis of Assisi Church should be leaving as its legacy on Maple Street.

If there is any way you can use your voice to urge the Diocese to come to the table — to respond to Council Member Joseph and Assemblymember Cunningham, to meet with this community, to consider a shorter building — we are asking you to do that now.

Thank you,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
          <EmailBlock id="email-diocese-3" to="Vincent LeVien, Director of External Affairs, Diocese of Brooklyn" toEmail="vlevien@desalesmedia.org" subject="Urgent Community Concern: 331 Maple St Development" body={`Dear Mr. LeVien,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a resident of Prospect Lefferts Gardens writing to urge the Diocese of Brooklyn to engage with our community on the proposed development at 331 Maple St.

As Director of External Affairs, I am reaching out to you directly because the Diocese's silence has become part of the story. Council Member Rita Joseph and Assemblymember Brian Cunningham have been requesting a high-level meeting with Diocese leadership for over a month with no response. Meanwhile, demolition of the 335 Maple St. Parish School — built in 1909 — is imminent.

More than 600 residents have signed a petition opposing this development. The community is not opposed to all development — we are opposed to a 12-story, 99-unit market-rate tower with zero affordable units that is wildly out of scale with a historic neighborhood. A compromise is still possible, but only if the Diocese chooses to engage.

I am asking you to facilitate that engagement. Please bring this message to Bishop Brennan and urge a response to the meeting requests from our elected representatives before it is too late.

Thank you,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-trigger">
          <span class="acc-label"><span class="acc-tag">City Hall</span> Mayor's Community Affairs Unit</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <EmailBlock id="email-mayor" to="Via nyc.gov/site/cau contact form or call 311" toLink="https://nyc.gov/site/cau" subject="Urgent Community Concern: 331 Maple St Development, Prospect Lefferts Gardens" body={`Hello,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a resident of Prospect Lefferts Gardens reaching out to the Mayor's Community Affairs Unit regarding an urgent development issue in my neighborhood.

St. Francis of Assisi Church on Nostrand Ave has entered into a 99-year lease with private equity-backed developer Candor Capital to construct a 12-story, 118-foot, 99-unit market-rate apartment complex at 331 Maple St. The current plans include zero affordable housing units. Not one. The existing 335 Maple St. Parish School will be demolished to make way for it, and demolition could begin at any time.

Over 600 residents have signed a petition opposing it. The Diocese of Brooklyn has refused to engage meaningfully. Council Member Rita Joseph and Assemblymember Brian Cunningham have been requesting a high-level meeting with Diocese leadership for over a month with no response.

I am asking the Mayor's office to intervene: pressure the Diocese to meet with elected officials, support a DOB review of the project's legality before demolition begins, and signal support for contextual zoning protections for PLG.

Thank you,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-trigger">
          <span class="acc-label"><span class="acc-tag">City Council</span> Council Member Rita Joseph</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <EmailBlock id="email-rita" to="rjoseph@council.nyc.gov | CC: JDesouve@council.nyc.gov" toEmail="rjoseph@council.nyc.gov" subject="Urgent Request: Intervention on 331 Maple St and Contextual Rezoning for PLG" body={`Dear Council Member Joseph,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a proud resident of Prospect Lefferts Gardens writing to urge you to take action on two related issues: the immediate crisis at 331 Maple St, and the long-overdue need for contextual zoning protections for our neighborhood.

I know your office is already engaged on 331 Maple St, and I am deeply grateful for that. The fact that you and Assemblymember Cunningham have been requesting a high-level meeting with the Diocese of Brooklyn for over a month without a response is itself a story. The community sees it, appreciates your persistence, and is doing everything we can to amplify the pressure alongside you.

FIRST: IMMEDIATE ACTION ON 331 MAPLE ST

With demolition of the Maple Street Parish School imminent, I am asking your office to escalate in every way available. Please formally request that the NYC Department of Buildings halt demolition pending a full review of the FAR calculations, open space ratios, and any lot merging or air rights transfers. Please continue pressing the Diocese for a meaningful meeting with actual decision-makers. Please consider a formal call for a Community Benefits Agreement requiring a significantly reduced building height and meaningful affordable housing — the current plan includes zero.

SECOND: CONTEXTUAL REZONING STUDY FOR PLG

331 Maple St is not an isolated incident. It is the predictable consequence of leaving PLG without the contextual zoning protections that Park Slope, Windsor Terrace, and Kensington have had for years. Our zoning parameters were last updated in 1961.

Respectfully,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-trigger">
          <span class="acc-label"><span class="acc-tag">State Assembly</span> Assemblymember Brian Cunningham</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <EmailBlock id="email-cunningham" to="cunninghamba@nyassembly.gov" toEmail="cunninghamba@nyassembly.gov" subject="Urgent Request: State-Level Action on 331 Maple St and Contextual Rezoning for PLG" body={`Dear Assemblymember Cunningham,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a resident of Prospect Lefferts Gardens writing to urge you to use every tool available at the state level to intervene on the proposed 12-story development at 331 Maple St.

I know your office has been requesting a meeting with the Diocese of Brooklyn alongside Council Member Joseph for over a month with no response. The community sees that. We are grateful, and we need you to keep pushing.

The developer, Candor Capital, allegedly showed the Church a 6-story mock-up before signing the lease, then secretly filed for 12 stories with DOB. Illegal demolition has already been attempted — a Stop Work Order was issued and violated repeatedly, resulting in $30,000 in fines. The Diocese has stonewalled every attempt at dialogue.

I am asking your office to use its state-level leverage to pressure the Diocese of Brooklyn to engage, support a formal DOB review of the project's legality before demolition proceeds, and advocate for a contextual rezoning study for PLG. Park Slope, Windsor Terrace, and Kensington all have height protections. PLG has been requesting the same since 2008.

Respectfully,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-trigger">
          <span class="acc-label"><span class="acc-tag">City Agency</span> NYC Department of Buildings</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <EmailBlock id="email-dob" to="buildings@buildings.nyc.gov or via nyc.gov/buildings" toEmail="buildings@buildings.nyc.gov" subject="Formal Concern: Air Rights and Development Legality at 331 Maple St, Brooklyn" body={`Hello,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a Prospect Lefferts Gardens resident writing to raise a formal concern about the proposed development at 331 Maple St, Brooklyn, NY 11225.

St. Francis of Assisi Church has entered into a 99-year lease with developer Candor Capital for a 12-story, 118-foot, 99-unit market-rate apartment complex at this address. The site is in an R6 zone where a 118-foot building requires very specific open space ratios and FAR calculations. The property carries 122,180 square feet of additional air rights for a total buildable of 144,828 square feet, but how those rights are being deployed has not been publicly accounted for.

I am requesting that DOB conduct a thorough review of the FAR calculations, open space ratios, and any air rights transfers before any demolition or construction proceeds.

Over 600 residents have signed a petition opposing this development. Council Member Rita Joseph and Assemblymember Brian Cunningham are actively engaged. I ask that DOB take the community's concerns seriously and ensure full legal compliance.

Thank you,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-trigger">
          <span class="acc-label"><span class="acc-tag">City Planning</span> DCP Director Sideya Sherman</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <EmailBlock id="email-dcp" to="ssherman@planning.nyc.gov | CC: BK_DL@planning.nyc.gov" toEmail="ssherman@planning.nyc.gov" subject="Urgent Request: DOB Review of 331 Maple St and Contextual Rezoning Study for PLG" body={`Dear Director Sherman,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a Prospect Lefferts Gardens resident writing to request urgent action on two related matters: an immediate DOB review of a proposed development at 331 Maple St, and the initiation of a long-overdue contextual rezoning study for PLG.

St. Francis of Assisi Church has entered into a 99-year lease with developer Candor Capital to build a 12-story, 118-foot, 99-unit market-rate apartment complex at 331 Maple St. The plans include zero affordable units. The site is in an R6 zone where a 118-foot building requires very specific open space ratios and FAR calculations. I am asking DCP to formally request that DOB review the calculations before demolition proceeds.

PLG is one of the last neighborhoods bordering Prospect Park without contextual zoning protections. Park Slope, Windsor Terrace, and Kensington all have height caps. PLG does not. Its zoning was last updated in 1961, and the community has been formally requesting a contextual rezoning study from DCP since 2008. I am asking you to take that step.

Thank you,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-trigger">
          <span class="acc-label"><span class="acc-tag">Local</span> Community Board 9 &amp; Public Advocate</span>
          <span class="accordion-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <EmailBlock id="email-cb9" to="Community Board 9" toEmail="bk09@cb.nyc.gov" subject="Request for CB9 Action: 331 Maple St Development" body={`Hello,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a Prospect Lefferts Gardens resident writing to urge Community Board 9 to formally weigh in on the proposed development at 331 Maple St.

More than 600 community members have signed a petition opposing this project. Despite this, the Diocese of Brooklyn has refused to engage meaningfully. Demolition of the existing 335 Maple St. Parish School is imminent.

I want to note that CB9's own Zoning Framework, passed in 2024, calls for infill buildings to be the same height as other buildings where there is a consistent streetscape. Maple Street is exactly such a streetscape — a block of single-family homes and prewar buildings no more than 4–5 stories tall. A 12-story, 118-foot tower is a direct violation of the principles CB9 has already gone on record supporting.

I am asking Community Board 9 to pass a formal resolution opposing this development as currently proposed, request that DOB review the project's FAR calculations and air rights transfers before demolition proceeds, and use CB9's advisory role to put on record that this community demands both a reduced building height and meaningful affordable housing commitments.

Thank you,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
          <EmailBlock id="email-advocate" to="Via advocate.nyc.gov/contact" toLink="https://advocate.nyc.gov/contact" subject="Request for Intervention: 331 Maple St Development, PLG Brooklyn" body={`Hello,

My name is [YOUR NAME], and I am a Prospect Lefferts Gardens resident writing to request the Public Advocate's intervention in an urgent development matter.

St. Francis of Assisi Church has entered into a 99-year lease with developer Candor Capital to build a 12-story, 118-foot, 99-unit market-rate apartment complex at 331 Maple St with zero affordable housing units. The developer has already attempted illegal demolition — workers began tearing down the 1909 parish school without permits in January. A Stop Work Order was issued and has been violated repeatedly, resulting in $30,000 in fines. The Diocese has refused to engage with the community or its elected representatives for months.

Over 600 residents have signed a petition. I am asking the Public Advocate's office to take three specific actions: publicly call on the Diocese of Brooklyn to meet with Council Member Joseph and Assemblymember Cunningham; request that DOB halt demolition pending a full legal review of the project's FAR calculations and air rights; and investigate whether the property's tax-exempt status is appropriate given that it is being leased to a private developer for luxury housing with zero affordable units.

Thank you,
[YOUR NAME]
Prospect Lefferts Gardens, Brooklyn`} />
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── HOW TO HELP ─── -->
<section class="help-section" id="help">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="section-label">How to Help</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Every action <em>counts.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="help-grid">
      <HelpCard num="01" title="Email the Diocese" body="Contact Bishop Robert Brennan, Father Vassalotti, and the Diocese directly. A personal email from a constituent lands in a real inbox and demands a real response." linkHref="#emails" linkLabel="Get Email Templates" />
      <HelpCard num="02" title="Contact Elected Officials" body="Email Council Member Rita Joseph and Assemblymember Brian Cunningham. They're already fighting — let them know the community is behind them and urge escalation." linkHref="#emails" linkLabel="See Templates" />
      <HelpCard num="03" title="Sign the Petition" body="Over 600 neighbors have already signed. Your name and address show the impact is real and local — and the number sends a message to everyone watching." linkHref="#petition" linkLabel="Sign Now" />
      <HelpCard num="04" title="Spread the Word" body="Post on Instagram, send to your group chats, forward to anyone who lives in or loves PLG. Every share reaches a new network — and this campaign grows one conversation at a time." linkHref={null} linkLabel={null} shareBtn={true} />
      <HelpCard num="05" title="File a DOB Complaint" body="Contact the NYC Department of Buildings and formally request a review of the FAR calculations, open space ratios, and air rights transfers before any demolition proceeds." linkHref="https://nyc.gov/buildings" linkLabel="NYC Buildings Site" external={true} />
      <HelpCard num="06" title="Show Up in Person" body="A Sunday demonstration outside St. Francis of Assisi at 1081 Nostrand Ave during Mass is one of the most visible ways to put pressure on church leadership. Bring neighbors." linkHref="#contacts" linkLabel="Get the Address" />
      <HelpCard num="07" title="Join the Effort" body="Want to canvass, attend meetings, or help organize? This campaign runs on neighbors showing up for neighbors. Reach out and get involved." linkHref="#" linkLabel="Contact Amy" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── KEY CONTACTS ─── -->
<section class="contacts-section" id="contacts">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="section-label">Key Contacts</p>
